deck_excerpt: This deck has link combos AND Xyz combos in the OCG, but over here we've gotta rely on more archaic methods of OTKing the opponent. You end up sitting
deck_description: Essentially you want to make big plays with the unholy insect trinity of Inzektor Dragonfly, Inzektor Hornet, and Inzektor Giga-Mantis. Because two of these three play makers are at one, however, we have to get creative in alternative plays and consistency that doesn't harm this very specific combo deck. The Summoner Monk 'engine' provides a consistency boost in discarding dead spells (including Metalfoes Fusion, a spell that let's you draw 1 by shuffling it from the grave into the deck) to summon Armageddon Knight, which can dump a Farfa for some light removal or an Inzektor piece, or maybe a hopper to facilitate hornet, then make a rank 4 play. Overall a super fun strategy that will (hopefully) get a significant boost with its new link monster.
The deck controls the game using Traps and Frogs to get out Toadally Awesome.
The goal of the deck is to put pressure on board with a variety of powerful Machine-type Main and Extra Deck monsters.
Try to get all 5 pieces asap and use card trader to get rid of stuff you don't want.

Monsters:

Astrograph Sorcerer: Astrograph Sorcerer is used to + after you use Wavering Eyes, simply activate wavering eyes, search Astrograph Sorcerer, then activate Astrograph Sorcerer's effect and get a free card (Can also be used if you need the scale but I don't recommend unless it's your only play).   Oafdragon Magician: Oafdragon Magician allows you to get a free card back, often Harmonizing Magician but also useful to bring back a scale.   Performpal Skullcrobat Joker: Performpal Skullcrobat Joker gives you a free search, a good strategy is to search Harmonizing Magician and then Pendulum Summoning it out. Black Fang Magician: Black Fang Magician is a floater and a High Scale, you can Special Summon him from the deck using Harmonizing Magician's effect and use him as XYZ material (I recommend another Dark Spellcaster, this allows you to special summon him from another Black Fang Magician's effect and then use his effect to Special Summon the other Dark Spellcaster you used, this grants some decent stall if needed or just more material after you pop it with Time Pendulumgraph), this stops him from being banished and provides free material for his effect. White Wing Magician: White Wing Magician is used as a Low Scale when you have no other options (Or just when you're against a match-up that might target a Dark Spellcaster you control), she is also used as a tuner to go into double Psy-Framelord Omega. Wisdom-Eye Magician: Wisdom-Eye Magician provides a free Scale and he can be Pendulum Summoned afterwards as extra material. Double Iris Magician: Double Iris Magician is your go to High Scale and great for searching out your Pendulumgraph's. Performpal Pendulum Sorcerer: Performpal Pendulum Sorcerer allows you to not only destroy your scales but search Performpal Skullcrobat Joker for another search (Keep in mind that you can destroy both of your Scales to Search Performpal Skullcrobat Joker and your second copy of Performpal Pendulum Sorcerer). Purple Poison Magician: Purple Poison Magician is your general go to Low Scale, he provides removal when he is destroyed and can boost your Dark Spellcaster's attack to Beat over things. Harmonizing Magician: Harmonizing Magician provides you with a free XYZ or Synchro Summon. Ash Blossom and Joyous Spring, Ghost Ogre and Snow Rabbit & Maxx "C": These are your Hand Traps; Destruction, Negates and Draw Power, very useful cards for stopping your Opponent.

Spells:

Pot of Desires: Pot of Desires is used to boost your consistency and give you some Card Advantage. Duelist Alliance: Duelist Alliance allows you to search Double Iris Magician, Performpal Pendulum Sorcerer, Space Pendulumgraph or Time Pendulumgraph. Cosmic Cyclone: Cosmic Cyclone is great S/T Removal. Wavering Eyes: Wavering Eyes is used to Destroy your Scales, Search your Astrograph Sorcerer and if your Opponent is playing Pendulums you can Banish a card they Control then Search another Wavering Eyes. Space Pendulumgraph: Space Pendulumgraph provides you with a free Search when one of your Magician Pendulum Monster's leaves the Field (Usually by Battle, Scale Destruction Effects or when you Synchro Summon).

Traps:

Time Pendulumgraph: Time Pendulumgraph provides you with Protection again threats, it can also be used with Timestar Magician to stop the Destruction of the card you Target giving you both the Destruction and Send Effect.   Extra Deck: Scarlight Red Dragon Archfiend: Scarlight Red Dragon Archfiend gives you a potential Board Clear and Burn, he's also a Beater which is nice. Ignister Pominence, the Blasting Dracoslayer: Ignister Prominence, the Blasting Dracoslayer provides you the ability to Destroy one of your Pendulum Monsters and then Shuffle one of your Opponent's cards into the Deck. Psy-Framelord Omega: Psy-Framelord Omega is one of your go to Extra Deck Monsters, he can Banish himself to take away one of your Opponent's Cards in their Hand and bring himself back next turn in the Main Monster Zone. Supreme King Dragon Clear Wing: Supreme King Dragon Clear Wing provides a potential Board Clear and Once Per Turn he has the ability to Destroy a Monster he Battles and Inflict Damage to your Opponent equal to the Destroyed Monster's Attack. Enlightenment Paladin: Enlightenment Paladin gives you a free Spell Card and some potential Burn Damage. Supreme King Dragon Dark Rebellion: Supreme King Dragon Dark Rebellion is a huge Beater, Once Per Turn when he Battles and Opponent's Monster he can reduce the Monster's Attack to 0 and gain it until the End Of The Turn (This equates to Damage to your Opponent equal to 2500 + the Opponent's Monster's Attack). Performage Trapeze Magician: Performage Trapeze Magician is an OTK enabler. Timestar Magician: Timestar Magician gives you Search and stops the Destruction of a Pendulum Monster. Tornado Dragon: Tornado Dragon is great on demand S/T Removal. Number 41: Bagooska The Terribly Tired Tapir: Number 41: Bagooska The Terribly Tired Tapir is a Stall card and one of your go to Extra Deck Monsters. Castel, the Skyblaster Musketeer: Castel, the Skyblaster Musketeer is some great on demand Removal. Abyss Dweller: Abyss Dweller stops your Opponent's Graveyard Effects from Activating. Decode Talker: Decode Talker enables you to pump out more Extra Deck Monsters, Pendulum Monsters and Beat over one of your Opponent's Monsters.   Side Deck and Tips coming sometime soon.

-Livid

deck_description:
As this deck is not one of the top and the graydle combo consumed only half of the deck, the other half is focused on  keeping yourself alive by denying attacks and monster effects for good.

You can use Book of Moon to unequip a graydle monster without losing the enemy monster, in case you need the S/T place or the monster in the GY.

If your Lose 1 Turn is on the field, you must fous on monster stealing only.

If your Skill Drain is on the field, don't use your tuners unless you are really sure its worth it. Combo a Graydle Dragon Synchro Summon with Skill Drain/Lose 1 Turn and Book of Moon for surprise 2-3 card destruction.

Cardcar D is for emergency or bad first hand only. Don't use it if you can do anything.

Thats all. Really simple strategy. Keep your opponent down.

deck_excerpt: A hybrid Buster Blader / Red-Eyes deck, my first attempt to build a deck on my own. Needs criticism and improvement.
deck_description:
My first attempt to build a deck on my own instead of copying other peoples'.

The main idea here is to use Buster Blader, Red-Eyes B. Dragon, and their respective supports to fusion summon powerful monsters such as Red-Eyes Flare Metal Dragon and Buster Blader, the Dragon Destroyer Swordsman (and crucially the Buster Dragon, as this will make all your opponents' cards Dragon-type and thereby buff your Buster Bladers), then use those monsters' effects as well as several trap cards to recall the fusion material from the graveyard.

 

Note: I'm aware 15 cards that should be in the Extra Deck are instead in the Main Deck, this is because for some reason the deck builder wouldn't let me add them to the Extra Deck where they belong.
